'''Scotland's Charity Air Ambulance''' is an organisation which will provide [[emergency medical services]] through the provision of a [[helicopter]] [[air ambulance]] covering the whole of [[Scotland]], [[United Kingdom]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.scaa.org.uk/who-we-are/|title=SCAA - Scotland's Charity Air Ambulance - About us|accessdate=27 Nov 2012|work=SCAA}}</ref> The helicopter will be run by a [[charitable organization|registered charity]], hoping to raise money from public and private donations in excess of Â£1.5 million every year.

The air ambulance will work alongside and complement the state-funded aircraft that presently operate in Scotland.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.scottishambulance.com/newsDesk/NewsItem.aspx?NewsID=39|title=Charity Air Ambulance for Scotland|accessdate=27 Nov 2012|work=Scottish Ambulance Service}}</ref>
Scotland's Charity Air Ambulance is scheduled to commence operations in early 2013 and will comprise a [[MBB Bo 105|Bolkow 105]] airframe crewed by [[Scottish Ambulance Service]] [[paramedic]]s.{{update after|2013|07|01}} The aircraft is expected to be based at [[Perth Airport (Scotland)|Perth Airport]] and tasking will be from the SAS ambulance control centre at [[Cardonald]].

